column23: Moment Commentary

column22: Ackeem Auguste finds the perfect elevation as he goes over extra cover on a full length delivery outside off stump from Nivethan Radhakrishnan and gets a four during the first group stage match of the 2022 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 19.4, N Radhakrishnan to Auguste, FOUR runs Tossed up outside the off stump, drives in the air to the extra cover fence.

column22: Andre Fletcher makes full use of the Lasith Malinga full toss and hammers it on to the leg side for a four during the group stage match of the 2010 ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
column23: 16.2, Malinga to Fletcher, FOUR runs An attempted yorker gone wrong, ends up as a low full toss outside leg, dispatched towards cow corner for four

column22: Colin Ingram advances and excellently times the full length delivery from John Mooney and plays it in the gap between extra cover and mid off for a four during the group stage match of the 2011 ICC Men's Cricket World Cup.
column23: 27.2, Mooney to Ingram, FOUR runs He comes forward and gets the drive in the gap between extra cover and mid off, first boundary in ages

column22: Corbin Bosch makes just the connection that the angling delivery from Preston McSween needed and plays it towards the fine leg fence for a four during the group stage match of the 2014 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 32.6, McSween to Bosch, FOUR runs Tickles it fine to the fence for a boundary.

column22: Great use of the feet and the wrists by Devon Thomas as he places a fullish delivery from James Tredwell into the gap for a four during the group stage match of the 2011 ICC Men's Cricket World Cup.
column23: 14.6, Tredwell to Thomas, FOUR runs Wow, maybe this is why he's been promoted! Thomas stretches across to the off side and whips his wrists at the ball, pings off the bat, wide of long-on and races away for four. What placement!

column17: 2021 ICC Men's T20 WC Warm Up Matches
column22: Excellent spin bowling on display from Hayden Walsh as he beats the edge of Babar Azam's bat who advances but completely misses only to be stumped easily by the keeper during the group stage match of the 2021 ICC Men's T20 Warm Up matches.
column23: 11.5, st â€ Pooran b Walsh

column22: A straighter one from Imad Wasim gets the better of Daryl Mitchell who goes for the big shot but ends up lofting it straight into the hands of long on during the group stage match of the 2021 ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
column23: 8.2, Imad Wasim to Mitchell, OUT this is the shot of a man who knows his time in the middle is done according to the tactics and he either hit out or get out. He tries it first ball, he tries it next ball too. This one is straighter so he takes on long-on this time. Finds the man to perfection

column22: Izharulhaq Naveed muscles the wide delivery from Qasim Akram over the head of the fielder at long on for a six during the group stage match of the 2022 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 41.3, Qasim Akram to Izharulhaq Naveed, SIX runs Tossed up, outside off, came down the wicket and flat hit over long-off fence for a big six

column22: Jayden Seales bangs it in short and generates the extra bounce to induce an edge off the bat of Bryce Parsons who is caught behind during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 6.2, Seales to B Parsons, OUT

column22: Smart batting from Jeavor Royal as he makes full use of the extra pace and bounce offered by Matthew Fisher and upper cuts the ball for a four down third man during the group stage match of the 2018 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 45.5, Fisher to Royal, FOUR runs

column22: Johnson Charles gets one in his slot from Mohammad Nabi and smokes it for a six over long on and into the stands during the group stage match of the 2016 ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
column23: 1.5, M Nabi to Charles, SIX runs wow - he's got all of this. He has utterly nailed it over wide long-on!

column22: Extra pace and bounce from Joshua James deceives Achille Cloete into playing a false shot only to get out caught at backward point during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 37.5, James to Cloete, OUT

column22: Keemo Paul's full delivery just outside off stump gets a healthy edge from the bat of Rahul Batham who is caught behind by the keeper during the final match of the 2016 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 45.1, Paul to Batham, OUT Paul wraps India up for 145. Gentle full ball outside off, nicked behind to Imlach who started it all off with some clever work behind the stumps

column22: A full length delivery from Hamidullah Qadri is hammered into the stands by Kirk McKenzie for a six during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 20.6, Hamidullah Qadri to McKenzie, SIX runs

column22: Kyle Mayers gets the big wicket of the Indian skipper Unmukt Chand who edges one straight to the wicket keeper during the group stage match of the 2012 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 19.3, Mayers to Chand, OUT The patience wears thin for Chand. After being pegged back by the deliveries in corridor, he decides to have a defensive poke at one and gets a faint outside edge back to the keeper. This time Ambris doesn't make any mistake.

column22: Cracking drive from Leonardo Julien as he times the full delivery just outside off stump from Blake Cullen through the covers for an elegant four during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 7.5, Cullen to Julien, FOUR runs

column22: A back of the hand slower one from Matthew Forde induces Kasey Aldridge into playing a big shot but he ends up skying it only to be caught by the bowler during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 42.3, Forde to Aldridge, OUT

column22: Nyeem Young goes for the attempted bouncer as Jesse Tashkoff shuffles across his stumps to connect but ends up gloving it to the keeper during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 15.1, Young to Tashkoff, OUT

column17: 2021 ICC Men's T20 WC Warm Up Matches
column22: Full and wide from Obed McCoy gets the better of Rahmanullah Gurbaz who goes for the big shot but doesnt get the connection it needed and ends up getting caught by the fielder in the deep during the 9th warm up match of the 2021 ICC Men's T20 World Cup Warm Up matches.
column23: 18.3, McCoy to Rahmanullah, OUT

column22: The Pakistan innings comes to an end as Oshane Thomas goes absolutely full and straight into the stumps of Wahab Riaz who ends but getting out bowled during the group stage match of the 2019 ICC Men's Cricket World Cup.
column23: 21.4, Thomas to Wahab Riaz, OUT Full, straight and gone! Such poor application. Why would you expose all three stumps and slog wildly when you have a lifetime of overs remaining?

column22: Preston McSween bowls the straight line and traps Yaseen Valli in front of his stumps as he tries to play across the line and ends up being adjudged lbw during the group stage match of the 2014 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 47.1, McSween to Valli, OUT Good ball in line with the stumps and Vallie looks to swing it over the midwicket fence, misses it and is struck on the pad, loud appeal and given.

column22: Qasim Akram flat bats the half tracker from Shevon Daniel with force over the extra cover fielder and into the gap for a four during the group stage match of the 2022 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 47.4, Daniel to Qasim Akram, FOUR runs Slaps it away over extra cover for a boundary

column22: Ramon Simmonds gets Jonathan Bird in two minds with his enticing line as Bird ends up edging one straight to the keeper during the group stage match of the 2020 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 3.3, Simmonds to Bird, OUT

column22: Lovely timing on display from Rivaldo Clarke as he gets one full and just outside off from William Salzmann and drives it well through covers for a four during the group stage match of the 2022 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 7.4, Salzmann to Clarke, FOUR runs Full and just outside off, comes well forward and drives it well in the gap between covers and extra cover for four

column22: Roston Chase gets an easy delivery short of length on leg stumps from Mustafizur Rahman as Chase manages to find the gap for a four depsite a diving attempt from the fielder during the group stage match of the 2021 ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
column23: 10.6, Mustafizur to Chase, FOUR runs Finally connects one. Short of a length on leg stump, goes back and across to smack a pull to deep square leg. Fielder running to his right had a shot at stopping it but couldn't parry it back in time

column22: The spinner from Sandeep Lamichhane induces Salman Fayyaz into playing a big shot but he fails to get the clearance and ends up getting caught at long on during the group stage match of the 2016 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 46.4, Lamichhane to Salman Fayyaz, OUT

column22: Seekkuge Prasanna bowls the pacy slider into the pads of Lendl Simmons on the first ball of his spell and finds Simmons plumb infront of his stumps during the semi final match of the 2014 ICC Men's T20 World Cup.
column23: 7.1, Prasanna to Simmons, OUT He takes the wicket of the first ball! That quick slider ends Simmons' innings. The batsman chose to stay back, but that one came in and came in quick and hit the back pad as the batsman looked to cut. That was an excellent delivery to start the spell.. A bit like Shahid Afridi's legspinners..

column22: Shamar Springer plays the perfect square drive against the wide delivery from Mason Crane to bring up a four during the group stage match of the 2016 ICC Men's Under 19 World Cup.
column23: 22.3, Crane to Springer, FOUR runs Flays that one into the point boundary. Gets to the pitch, opens the face of the bat and goes through with the square drive. Intent written all over that one
